rismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rzz1665702828501.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzz1665702828501.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzz1665702828501.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rzz1665702828501\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                          \n Define Hyperlink Properties\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define the properties of this hyperlink widget.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzz1665702828501__p_d9044e1_d9045e1_d9046e1\">For more information about hypelink widgets, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hta1665703126401.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hta1665703126401.html\" title=\"The uhyperlink widget is a display-only widget that acts like a hyperlink in a web page. It activates a command when the user clicks it. It can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called Hyperlink, which is mapped to uhyperlink.\">uhyperlink (Hyperlink)</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzz1665702828501__section_ckp_52k_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d697311e67\">How to</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzz1665702828501__p_d9062e1_d9063e1_d9064e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mae1704708062818.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mae1704708062818.html\" title=\"You can set widget properties in several ways—in the initialization file used by the application, in the IDE using the Properties Inspector, or in script. And you can set them in modeled entities, in component templates, in components, and in script.\">Setting Widget Properties</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div 